feed.title: Murray Sunset Np South Flora South Of Sturt Hwy

entry.title: Haloragis odontocarpa f. pterocarpa
entry.content: A few leaves seen throughout the NW at this time but only this plant with buds.

entry.title: Halgania cyanea
entry.content: One white among many blue-flowered plants.

entry.title: Acacia nyssophylla
entry.content: 20ish veins and gland well above leaf base distinguish this from A. colletioides.

entry.title: Cynoglossum australe
entry.content: Mericarps with barbed spines, inflorescence ebracteate.

entry.title: Ptilotus nobilis subsp. nobilis, Waitzia acuminata var. acumi...
Kippistia suaedifolia
entry.content: Masses at this location but only 100m or so either side, then nothing.

entry.title: Maireana radiata
entry.content: Small, appressed leaves on cottony stems. On pic2 the start of radiating veins just visible.

entry.title: Boronia coerulescens subsp. coerulescens, Laevicampsomeris fo...
entry.content: Wasp flying exclusively to Blue Boronia plants. Watched it for a few minutes.

entry.title: Calytrix spp.
entry.content: Awnless sepals and other features suggest C. alpestris but C. tetragona found nearby (see 10885) and alpestris not quite recorded in Murray-Sunset NP.

entry.title: Pimelea trichostachya
entry.content: Podotheca angustifolia in the background of pic 2.

entry.title: Hyalosperma spp.
entry.content: Either H. semisterile or H. glutinosum, most likely the former. Need fruit for ID. Location approximate.

entry.title: Podolepis rugata var. rugata
entry.content: Just make out the wrinkly/pleated bracts. Location approximate.

entry.title: Triodia scariosa
entry.content: A ring of plants- a formation this species often makes. Location approximate.

entry.title: Pterostylis mutica
entry.content: Can't see it can be anything else? Location approximate.

entry.title: Trachymene cyanopetala
entry.content: 3-6 fruit per umbel but not the usual bluish tinge. Location approximate.

entry.title: Castiarina spp., Waitzia acuminata var. acuminata
Phebalium bullatum
entry.content: Almost completely buried in sand but still flowering. Approximate location.

entry.title: Calytrix tetragona
entry.content: Almost buried in the sand. Approximate location.

entry.title: Eremophila glabra subsp. murrayana
entry.content: The fight for survival. Approximate location.

entry.title: Olearia rudis
entry.content: Only appears after fire. Approximate location.

entry.title: Eremophila glabra subsp. murrayana
entry.content: Growing among Waitzia acuminata. Approximate location.

entry.title: Glischrocaryon behrii
entry.content: 2nd pic shows mass display with Waitzia acuminata. Approximate location.

entry.title: Eremophila glabra subsp. murrayana
entry.content: Low, almost prostrate. Quite hairy this sample. Approximate location.

entry.title: Maireana radiata
entry.content: 2nd pic shows radiating veins from the centre of the fruit. Approximate location.

entry.title: Maireana pentatropis
entry.content: Zooming in you can just make out the hairy centre of the fruit. Approximate location.

entry.title: Senecio spanomerus
entry.content: Approximate location. Much debate over this one but weight of evidence suggests it is most likely S. spanomerus (not S. pinnatifolius var. pinnatifolius).

entry.title: Calotis cymbacantha
entry.content: Leaf shape is a distinguishing feature. Approximate location.

entry.title: Brachyscome ciliaris var. brachyglossa
entry.content: Note much-reduced ligules (petals) on this variety. Approximate location.

entry.title: Podolepis rugata var. rugata
entry.content: 2nd pic shows ID feature of the pleated bracts. Approximate location.

entry.title: Ptilotus spathulatus
entry.content: Shows creeping stems well. Approximate location.

entry.title: Podolepis capillaris
entry.content: Plant is almost invisible when not in flower. Waitzia acuminata in the back ground. 2nd pic by Doug Down. Approximate location.

entry.title: Harmsiodoxa blennodioides
entry.content: Fruit in 2nd pic is the key ID feature.

entry.title: Zygophyllum simile
entry.content: Not recorded anywhere near Pink Lakes previously. Small white flower top-right of pic shows 8 stamens, making it Z. simile.
